        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Put his hand to (ἐπιβαλὼν ἐπί)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Lit., having laid his hand upon.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Back (εἰς τὰ ὀπίσω)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Lit., to things behind. \"The figure is that of a man who, while engaged in labor, instead of keeping his eye on the furrow which he is drawing, looks behind at some object which attracts his interest. He is only half at work, and half-work only will be the result\" (Godet).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
